    "Gerson resigned in 1975 in order to revise his <em>Ausbreitung</em> book.": [],
    "However, he died suddenly at age 71 without completing it.": [],
    "A <a href=\"/gersonh\">Horst Gerson</a> lecture series was established in his memory at the University of Groningen.": [],
    "Gerson was at heart a connoisseur-style scholar--learned from his mentor <a href=\"/hofstededegrootc\">Cornelis Hofstede de Groot</a>--but one who blended an appreciation of documents, iconography, <em>Geistesgeschichte</em> and the Warburg Institute's conceptual-style art history into a cohesive method.": [],
    "Like any synthesizer, he attracted critics from all sides.": [],
    "<a href=\"/friedlanderm\">Max J. Friedl\u00e4nder</a> a connoisseur of a generation before, paid Gerson the back-handed compliment by quipping that of all the people he rejected, Gerson was the least aggregious (\"Von allen die verneinen, ist mir der Gerson noch am wenigsten zur Last\").": [],
